          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Edgar Fawcett</persname>to 
                  <persname>[Richard Henry ?]
                  Stoddard</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">[ante 1892] Jun 20</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>3 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Offers his new novel 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Adopted Daughter</bibref>with all
                  publication rights for one thousand dollars, about
                  which he says,"It is, of course, in a totally
                  different vein from either 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Douglas Duane</bibref>or 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Solarion</bibref>. It has cost me much toil
                  and thought, and I hope you will like what I fancy to
                  be its humanity and its general strong morale."]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
